1. Oil-based paints generally dry slower, allowing more time for adjustments and corrections during application.
2. The slower drying time of oil-based paints can make them easier to blend and smooth out.
3. Oil-based paints often require fewer coats, simplifying the painting process.
4. Cleanup for oil-based paints typically involves common solvents like mineral spirits, which are effective at removing paint from brushes and tools.
5. Brushes and rollers used with oil-based paints can be reused multiple times if cleaned properly with solvents.